{{About|the famous bull|the sports car|Lamborghini Islero}} {{Infobox animal | name = Islero | image = Islero manolete.jpg | image_size = | caption = | birth_name = | othername = | species = [[Spanish Fighting Bull]] | breed = [[Miura bull|Miura]] | gender = Male | birth_date = | birth_place = [[Seville]], [[Andalusia]], [[Spain]] | death_date = | death_place = | resting_place = | resting_place_coordinates = | relativeage = | nationality = [[Spain]] | occupation = | employer = | role = | years_active = | known = Gored and killed [[Manolete]] | tricks = | awards = | title = | term = | predecessor = | successor = | owner = Eduardo Miura Fernández | parents = | children = | weight = 495 Kg | height = | appearance = | namedafter = | website = }}
'''Islero''' was a [[Miura bull]] famed for killing the celebrated [[Bullfighting|bullfighter]] [[Manolete]] on August 28, 1947. Bulls from the Miura ranch, located near [[Seville]], Spain, are known for being large and ferocious.
Islero had poor eyesight and tended to chop with his right horn.<ref>https://web.archive.org/web/20080320224005/http://www.geocities.com/matador1920/manolete.htm</ref> On the fateful day, he was the fifth bull of the afternoon, and the second for Manolete, at a bullfight in the town of [[Linares, Jaén|Linares]] in the province of [[Jaén (Spanish province)|Jaén]], [[Andalucía]], Spain. The bull's manager begged Manolete to finish him off quickly; as the ''matador'' reached over the bull's horns, thrusting his ''estoque'' (sword) deep up to its hilt, Islero thrust his right horn into Manolete's groin, severing his [[femoral artery]]. The bullfighter was rushed to hospital, but died on the operating table later that evening.
Italian automaker [[Lamborghini]] named one of its [[grand tourer]]s "[[Lamborghini Islero|Islero]]" as part of the company's tradition of naming its cars after Miura bulls and with other bullfighting-related terms.
The Spanish project to build nuclear weapons was named Proyecto Islero.
