In [[embryology]], '''sturt''' is a measure of distance.  On the [[fate map]], the further apart two regions are, the more likely the resulting structures are to form different [[genotype]]s.  A difference of 1% in the ratio of differing genotypes is described as one sturt, after [[Alfred Henry Sturtevant]].

